arney reveals how racism has shaped our historical memory and neglected this critical African contribution to the making of the Americas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aRicexHistoryxAfrica, West. 0aRicexHistoryxSouthern States. 0aRicezAfrica, WestxHistory. 0aRicezSouthern StatesxHistory. 0aSlavesxSouthern StatesxAfrica, WestxSouthern StatesxWestafrikaxUSAxSüdstaaten. 0aSlavesxSouthern StatesxAfrica, WestxWestafrikaxUSAxSüdstaaten. 0aSlaveszSouthern States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)z978311075606708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674029217?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674029217423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674029217/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-075606-7  HUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013 (Canada)b2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK